lability sheet.  To qualify for employment in Student Centers as a building manager you must be:   Registered University of Illinois at Chicago Student for at least 6 credit hours  Two years of employment history or classified as a Sophomore student. Must be able to work early mornings, late evenings/nights, and on weekends. Must be able to work under minimum supervision. Must have a Valid Driver’s license and be able to successfully complete AED/First Aid Certification.  Student employees are both hired as regular and federal work study (FWS) employees. FWS students are given priority for job placement.       Applications        The Alley Application  To be considered to work in The Alley Bowling & Billiards, turn your application into the front desk at The Alley.          Building Management Application  Turn your application into the Building Managers office, located on the 1st floor of Student Centers              Bowling & Billiards    Back to main content           Hours    Rates and Reservations    Specials                  UIC Logo        Student Centers         Quick Links    Staff Directory    Student Employment    Feedback      Resources    Lockers Info and Policy    Bicycle Repair    Donation Bins      Tools    Building Directory    BM Reports    Operations Reports        BUTTON    Policies    Sustainability    Hours & Locations         Contact   scenters@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 